## Step 1: Launch EC2 Instance
- AMI: Amazon Linux
- Instance type: t2.micro
- Allow HTTP (80)
- Allow SSH (22) (optional)

## Step 2: Add User Data Script
- Go to Advanced details
- Paste boot script in User Data section
===========================================================================================================
                    #!/bin/bash
                    yum update -y
                    yum install httpd -y
                    systemctl start httpd
                    systemctl enable httpd

                    echo "<h1>Website Booted Automatically on EC2</h1>" > /var/www/html/index.html
============================================================================================================

## Step 3: Launch Instance
- Start the instance
- Wait 2â€“3 minutes for boot process

## Step 4: Access Website
- Copy Public IPv4 address
- Open browser:
  http://<public-ip>

## Step 5: Verify
- Website loads without manual installation
